# HTML Code Style — Яндекс.Практикум

## Indentation & Encoding
- Use 2 spaces for indentation. Never use tabs or mixed indentation.
- Always declare `<meta charset="utf-8">` in HTML documents.
- Save all files in UTF-8 encoding.

## Case
- Write ALL HTML code in lowercase: element names, attributes, attribute values (except text content in alt/title).
- No uppercase tags like `<DIV>` or `<A HREF>` — this is considered old school.

## Doctype & Validation
- Always start HTML documents with `<!DOCTYPE html>` (HTML5).
- Do not use XHTML syntax. Write valid HTML5.
- Validate HTML with W3C validator. Fix all structural and syntax errors.

## Semantics
- Use semantic elements for their purpose: `<h1>`–`<h6>` for headings, `<p>` for paragraphs, `<a>` for links, `<button>` for buttons.
- Never use `<div>` with onClick where a `<a>` or `<button>` would be correct.

## Multimedia
- Always add meaningful `alt` attribute to every `<img>`. 
- For decorative images use empty alt: `alt=""`.
- Add transcripts or subtitles to video/audio where possible.

## Separation of Concerns
- HTML files contain only markup. No inline styles (`style=""`). No inline JavaScript handlers.
- All styling goes to CSS files. All behavior goes to JS files.

## Quotes
- Use double quotes `""` for all HTML attribute values. Never single quotes.
```html
  <!-- Wrong -->
  <a class='btn'>Click</a>
  <!-- Correct -->
  <a class="btn">Click</a>
```

## Self-Closing Tags
- Do NOT self-close void elements. Write `<br>`, `<img>`, `<input>`, not `<br />` or `<img />`.

## Line Formatting
- Write each block, list, and table element on a new line.
- Indent each child element relative to its parent.
- Break long lines (long attribute lists). Continuation lines must be indented at least 2 spaces from the opening tag.
```html
  
    href="https://yandex.ru"
    class="my-link"
    target="_blank"
  >Link text</a>
```

## Entities
- When using UTF-8, do NOT use HTML entities like `&mdash;`, `&rdquo;`, `&#x263a;`.
- Exception: always escape `<` as `&lt;`, `>` as `&gt;`, `&` as `&amp;`, and use `&nbsp;` for non-breaking spaces.

## Resource Loading
- Use `type` attribute on `<script>` and `<link>` is NOT needed in HTML5. Omit it.
- Only load CSS and JS files that are actually used on the page. Remove unused `<link>` and `<script>` tags.
- Always use HTTPS for all external resources (scripts, styles, fonts, images).

## Comments & TODO
- Comment logical sections to explain structure. Mark open questions with `TODO(name@mail.com): description`.

## Trailing Whitespace
- No trailing spaces at end of lines.
- File must end with a single newline.
